ratings.comment: Victoria is very helpful and wants her students to understand the material. She tries to make concepts as clear as possible in lecture and will give especially helpful hints for the exam during the exam review sessions. She seemed a little nervous during lectures, but overall she is off to a great start as a professor. I would take Victoria again.

Victoria is an excellent instructor. She's only a grad student and probably has a lot on her plate and she still gives so much time to the students. Her lectures are very clear and organized, has very popular office hours each week for homework and quiz help, which can be really tricky but overall doable, and no Friday class. Go to exam reviews!

Excellent Instructor! Since she is a grad student she seems to understand what it is like to be a student. Super helpful and approachable. Would recommend going to all optional exam reviews and office hours as it is extremely helpful for the exams! If you do the homework, and make good notecards for exams an A is definitely doable in this class!

Very helpful , gives great noted and recaps after every lecture!  GO TO EXAM REVIEWS, they can make or break your exam grade! Quizzes can be tough but go in and ask questions and you'll be fine.  She is adorable and very understanding!

She's very nice and definitely understands what it is like to be a student. Teaches the class really well and gives out a lot of help during office hours and is always recommendable. The class is very fair and you can do well as long as you put in enough effort
She's awesome. Cool person and great teacher! Really clear and organized. Super accommodating also. Highly recommend taking this class. If you do the work you'll and go to class you can get an A.
she is very nice and organized! explained things well and clearly! highly recommended :)
